        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 11:44PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 1144 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Camp Springs, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Reidsville...
Yanceyville...
Bethel...
Providence...
Jericho...
Camp Springs...
and Prospect Hill.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
